PRIVACY POLICY
Updated on: July 13, 2024
Effective Date: July 13, 2024

INTRODUCTION
Welcome to eSOONTECH apps developed by Soontaek Lee.
This privacy policy clarifies what information is collected from the user when using eSOONTECH apps, who collects it, how it might be used, and what rights the user has in relation to it.
By using eSOONTECH apps, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this privacy policy and agree to the data practices outlined herein.
Please read carefully, and if there are any terms that you do not agree with, please uninstall and discontinue using eSOONTECH apps.

Definitions
• "App" refers to all eSOONTECH apps.
• "User" refers to anyone using the app.
• "Developer" refers to Soontaek Lee, the individual responsible for the development and maintenance of the app.

INFORMATION AND DATA COLLECTION
The developer does not own a server or a database to store user data in any form. However, the app uses third-party services that do collect data in compliance with their privacy policies as described below:
• AdMob by Google: Used to monetize the app. Its data collection includes, but is not limited to, device information, location data, and advertising identifiers.
• User Messaging Platform: Used to comply with relevant regulations, such as the GDPR, by displaying Consent Messages on the app. Its data collection includes, but is not limited to, IP address, Android advertising ID.

COLLECTION PURPOSE
The data is collected for the following purposes:
• To show personalized or non-personalized ads depending on the device configuration of the user.
• To comply with relevant data protection laws and regulations, including the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), where applicable after determining if the consent message should be shown based on the user’s location and to manage the consent for data collection according to the user’s consent.
• To improve the app’s performance in future updates.

DATA HANDLING
The collected data is handled by the third-party services mentioned above, the developer may access them only via their consoles, and does not copy or share or sell this data.
For information regarding how Google uses information and data from sites or apps that use its services, please refer to this link for more details:
https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites
Please note that Google’s privacy policy is different, refer to this link for more details:
https://policies.google.com/privacy

USER RIGHTS
The user has the following rights concerning the data collected by the third-party services mentioned above:
• The right to access personal data collected by AdMob.
• The right to request the deletion of personal data.
• The right to know what data is being collected and how it is being used.
• The right to opt-out of personalized advertising by adjusting ad settings on the device or by visiting Google's Ads Settings (please refer to the steps in Google’s support page: https://support.google.com/ads/answer/2662856?co=GENIE.Platform%3DAndroid&oco=1 or simply use the "Opt-Out Of Ads Personalization" option in the setting of the app).
For more information on how to exercise these rights, please visit Google’s Privacy Policy:
https://policies.google.com/privacy

THIRD-PARTY SERVICES
The app may contain links to other sites. If the user clicks on a third-party link, they will be directed to that site. These external sites are not operated by the developer of the app. Therefore, it is strongly advised to review the Privacy Policy of these websites. The developer of the app has no control over and assumes no responsibility for the content, privacy policies, or practices of any third-party sites or services.

MODIFICATION OF PRIVACY POLICY
The developer may modify the policy at any time. The change will be mentioned in the “What’s new” section of Play Store and “Changelog” section in the app. Your continued use of the app after changes have been made constitutes acceptance of the new policy. Reviewing the Privacy Policy periodically for any changes is encouraged.
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact the developer at esoontech@gmail.com.
